tm2/pkg/amino/json_test.go
442:func (cm customJSONMarshaler) MarshalJSON() ([]byte, error) {
```

#### Description
The following code snippet compiles and runs successfully in Gno, which is incorrect behavior:

```go
package main

func main() {
	t := struct{}
}
```

#### Expected Behavior
This code should not compile because a type cannot be assigned as a value in Gno.

https://github.com/gnolang/gno/blob/2838ad1a3c3b9795990257cd46f08fc04b2fb3a3/tm2/pkg/os/tempfile.go#L110-L112 leak the created file

## Suggested remedy
Please use a defer and just check if f != nil so
```go
defer func() {
       if f != nil {
             f.Close()
             os.Remove(f.Name())
       }
}()
```

